When does a react component re-render ?
==> 1. When state changes :-
             If the components states updates , React re-renders the components.
               EX:-   const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
                  setCount(1);

                  When setCount is called :- 
                   1. React updates the state .
                   2. The component function runs again .
                   3. UI updates if needed .

         React only re-renders if the state value actually changes.

==> 2. When props changes :-
            If a parent component passes new props , the child components re-renders .
               <Child name="Pratibha" />
               If the parents changes it to :-
               <Child name ="Rahul"  />
               child will re-render because props changes.


==> 3. When Parent Components re-renders :-
             Even if props don't change , a child component re-renders if parent component re-renders .
              EX :- 
                 function parent() {
                      const [count , setCount] = useState(0) ;
                      return <Child />
                 } 
               When parent re-renders -> Child also re-renders .
                To avoid unnecessary re-renders, React provides:
                 React.memo()

==>  4. When context value changes :-
            If a component uses React Context , it re-renders when the context value changes .
              EX :- 
                   const theme = useContext(ThemeContext);
                   If ThemeContext value updates → component re-renders.


==> 5. When forceUpdate is called class component :-
            In class components:
                  this.forceUpdate();
            This forces a re-render even if nothing changed.


   A re-render does not mean the DOM updates immediately :-
        React 
          1. Re-runs components . 
          2. Creates virtual DOM .  
          3. Compares with previous DOM .
          4. Updates only the changed part .

          This makes react fast and efficient .

      How to prevent unnecessary re-renders in React ?
       ==> To prevent unnecessary re-renders in React like :-
            1. useMemo
            2. React.memo
            3. useCallBack 